$ System.Windows.Media.Visual (abstract class)

`System.Windows.Media.Visual` derives from → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Windows/DependencyObject[`System.Windows.DependencyObject`].

In WPF, `Visual` provides rendering, hit testing, coordinate transformation and bounding box calculations.
-
Apparently, `Visual` comes close to the concept of → Windows/development/WinAPI/data-types#windef-h-HWND[`HWND`].

`Visual` connects the managed part of WPF with the unmanaged *milcore* (DirectX).
